---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../../components/PageHero";
import buddhimanImg from "../../assets/images/team/buddhiman-tamang.webp";
import buddhimanBlogImg from "../../assets/images/team/buddhiman-blog-origin.webp";

const article = {
    title: "Why We Left the Guidebook Behind",
    subtitle: "The Origin Story",
    heroImage: buddhimanImg.src,
    date: "December 31, 2025",
    author: "Buddhiman Tamang",
    readTime: "4 min read",
};
---

<Layout
    title={article.title}
    description="It started with a realization at 5,000 meters. Discover the philosophy and origin story of Marga Adventure."
    image={article.heroImage}
>
    <PageHero
        title="The Origin"
        subtitle="Why we walked away from the ordinary."
        image={article.heroImage}
        parallax={true}
    />

    <article class="py-24 px-6 md:px-12 lg:px-24 bg-white">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
            {/* Header Info */}
            <div
                class="flex items-center justify-between border-b border-gray-100 pb-8 mb-12"
            >
                <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                    <div
                        class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-gray-100 overflow-hidden"
                    >
                        <img
                            src={buddhimanImg.src}
                            alt="Boudha"
                            class="w-full h-full object-cover"
                        />
                    </div>
                    <div>
                        <p
                            class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-900"
                        >
                            {article.author}
                        </p>
                        <p
                            class="text-[10px] text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mt-1"
                        >
                            Founder & CEO
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="text-right">
                    <p class="text-xs font-bold text-gray-900">
                        {article.date}
                    </p>
                    <p
                        class="text-[10px] text-brand uppercase tracking-widest mt-1"
                    >
                        {article.readTime}
                    </p>
                </div>
            </div>

            {/* Content */}
            <div
                class="prose prose-lg prose-headings:font-serif prose-headings:font-bold prose-headings:text-gray-900 prose-p:text-gray-800 prose-blockquote:font-serif prose-blockquote:text-brand-dark prose-blockquote:not-italic prose-blockquote:border-brand max-w-none leading-loose"
            >
                <p
                    class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-900 font-serif italic mb-10 leading-relaxed border-l-4 border-brand pl-8 py-2"
                >
                    "It started with a realization at 5,000 meters, gasping for
                    air in the thin blue light: the summit is not the point. The
                    point is who you become on the way up."
                </p>

                <p
                    class="mb-8 first-letter:text-7xl first-letter:font-bold first-letter:text-brand first-letter:float-left first-letter:mr-4 first-letter:mt-[-10px]"
                >
                    For 16 years, I walked the trails of the Himalayas. I
                    carried heavy packs, I managed logistics, and I watched
                    thousands of people come to Nepal clutching a checklist.
                    They wanted to conquer Everest Base Camp. They wanted the
                    perfect sunrise shot at Poon Hill. They wanted to say, "I
                    did it." They were racing against time, checking off peaks
                    like items on a grocery list.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-8">
                    But I noticed something profound in the quiet moments
                    between the chaos. The people who left with tears in their
                    eyes the ones who were truly changed weren't the ones who
                    marched fastest. They were the ones who stopped.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-8">
                    They were the ones who sat on a cold stone wall to drink
                    salty butter tea with a grandmother in a village. They were
                    the ones who closed their eyes to listen to the wind
                    snapping the prayer flags, feeling the vibration of the
                    mantra in their bones. They were the ones who forgot about
                    the WiFi password and remembered their connection to their
                    own spirit.
                </p>

                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">
                    The Gap in the Soul
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-8">
                    Tourism has become an industry of extraction. We extract
                    experiences, we extract photos, and we leave, often
                    untouched. I wanted to build something different. With my
                    background in Psychology, I understood that travel is
                    actually a disguised search for meaning. In Sanskrit,
                    "Marga" means path, not just a physical trail, but a
                    spiritual journey.
                </p>
                <p class="mb-8">
                    That is why Marga Adventure was born. We threw away the
                    standard guidebook that tells you <em>what</em> to see. We wanted
                    to explore <em>how</em> to be. We don't just "do" treks. We facilitate
                    journeys. We combine high-altitude adventure with deep mindfulness.
                    We explicitly design moments of silence into our itineraries,
                    forcing you to confront the beauty of the present moment.
                </p>

                <div
                    class="my-16 relative rounded-3xl overflow-hidden h-[400px]"
                >
                    <img
                        src={buddhimanBlogImg.src}
                        alt="Himalayan landscape"
                        class="w-full h-full object-cover"
                        loading="lazy"
                        decoding="async"
                    />
                </div>

                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-12 mb-6">
                    The Invitation
                </h3>
                <p class="mb-8">
                    We are not for everyone. If you want to race to the top,
                    there are other agencies. But if you want to understand why
                    the Sherpa people bow to these peaks as gods, if you want to
                    understand the silence of your own mind, and if you want to
                    leave Nepal not just with photos, but with a new perspective
                    on life... then you are ready for the Marga.
                </p>
                <p>
                    We invite you to walk with us. Not just on the earth, but
                    into yourself.
                </p>
                <p>Welcome to the family.</p>
                <p class="mt-8 font-bold text-brand">— Buddhiman</p>
            </div>

            {/* Footer Nav */}
            <div
                class="mt-24 pt-12 border-t border-gray-100 flex justify-between items-center"
            >
                <a
                    href="/blog"
                    class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400 hover:text-brand transition-colors"
                    >← Back to Journal</a
                >
                <a
                    href="/blog/philosophy-of-silence"
                    class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-gray-400 hover:text-brand transition-colors"
                    >Next Story →</a
                >
            </div>
        </div>
    </article>
</Layout>
